S'\xe2\x80\x94 1 \xe2\x80\x94I\xe2\x80\x99ve usually avoided Drunk History (a show where heavily in their cups historians summarize a notable life or event, and then have their garbled retellings reenacted by actors) because I saw an episode that involved vomiting, which I\xe2\x80\x99d prefer not to see.But this episode about Harriet Tubman\xe2\x80\x99s in the Civil War (about which I knew nothing, and in which she\xe2\x80\x99s played by Octavia Spencer) is excellent (and involves no sickness at all, no promises if you check out other episodes). \xe2\x80\x94 2 \xe2\x80\x94Speaking of unexpected good works, I found it really interesting to read through GiveWell\xe2\x80\x99s list of non-existent charities that they\xe2\x80\x99d like people to found so that they can fund them.Charities that implement GiveWell\xe2\x80\x99s\xc2\xa0priority programs: vitamin A supplementation, immunizations, conditional cash transfers, micronutrient fortification, or even bednets and deworming (since our top charities that focus on the latter two have limited room for more funding).\xc2\xa0More Charities implementing potential priority programs that are particularly challenging, particularly those revolving around (a) treatment of treatable conditions in a hospital or clinic setting; (b) behavior change for improving health. We see several hurdles to successfully focusing on such programs, but would be excited to see charities that overcome such hurdles.\xc2\xa0More Charities that collect or generate information and data relevant to our recommendations. Currently, we recommend charities based partly on the data they themselves collect and share. But we could potentially recommend an organization that does not, itself, collect and share strong monitoring data, if we had independent data showing its activities\xe2\x80\x99 effectiveness.\xc2\xa0MoreThey have a lot more details at the link.\xc2\xa0\xe2\x80\x94 3 \xe2\x80\x94GiveWell does a great job looking not only at what we know now, but at what we\xe2\x80\x99d need to learn more about charity effectiveness. \xc2\xa0Also in the vein of good epistemological practices, I liked this homework assignment:So, I\xe2\x80\x99m TAing an undergrad algorithms class, and this week they have a homework on dynamic programming.\xc2\xa0 And the first question is interesting, because it gives them a dynamic programming problem and asks them to find the solution, but it also gives them some algorithms that don\xe2\x80\x99t work, and asks them to find counterexamples.And this strikes me as a really useful homework problem, because the art of finding counterexamples is essential to writing algorithms; it\xe2\x80\x99s how you tell whether your algorithm actually works. \xc2\xa0(I mean, you can try proving it formally, and if the proof doesn\xe2\x80\x99t work, that can help you find flaws in your algorithm. \xc2\xa0But it\xe2\x80\x99s often much faster to think of a counterexample.) \xc2\xa0I remember that my undergrad algorithms professor was really good at finding counterexamples, and I was sort of awed by his ability to do so. \xc2\xa0But prior to this homework problem, I don\xe2\x80\x99t think I\xe2\x80\x99d ever seen anyone explicitly acknowledge counterexample-finding as a skill that needed to be practiced.(found via Mike Blume\xe2\x80\x99s tumblr)\xc2\xa0\xe2\x80\x94 4 \xe2\x80\x94From the annals of very clever engineering: Using synthetic DNA to authenticate paintings!The new approach, in its formative stage, would implant synthetic DNA, not the personal DNA of the artists, because of privacy issues and because a person\xe2\x80\x99s DNA could conceivably be stolen and embedded, thus undermining the authority of such a marking protocol.The developers said the bioengineered DNA would be unique to each item and provide an encrypted link between the art and a database that would hold the consensus of authoritative information about the work. The DNA details could be read by a scanner available to anyone in the art industry wanting to verify an object.\xe2\x80\x94 5 \xe2\x80\x94From the annals of very silly lifehacks: Body builders who spend time in a miniature village to feel even bigger!Here\xe2\x80\x99s how much Mallory Ortberg loved it, need you know more?Every moment is to be savored without explanation. Do not look for context. I don\xe2\x80\x99t ever want to know anything more about this video than I do right now. I don\xe2\x80\x99t care if it\xe2\x80\x99s a hoax, or a viral marketing ad for creatine, or anything else. I don\xe2\x80\x99t care.\xe2\x80\x94 6 \xe2\x80\x94Back to actual cleverness: I learned how to prove Fermat\xe2\x80\x99s Little Theorem in high school, but the method I learned was a lot fiddlier and less layperson friendly than this very nice method shown by Khan Academy. \xc2\xa0I promise you, there are no prereqs for this and it\xe2\x80\x99s delightfully done. \xe2\x80\x94 7 \xe2\x80\x94Finally, my life is still very all-Hamilton, all the time (a scandal on\xc2\xa0Borgen (a Danish political drama) prompted a chorus of\xc2\xa0\xe2\x80\x9cNever gon\xe2\x80\x99 be Statsminister now!\xe2\x80\x9d and my friends keep writing Paul Ryan-themed relyricizations as the House drama plays out).If the upshot of all this is that there\xe2\x80\x99s more of a market for implausible-on-paper musicals about historical figures, I am\xc2\xa0totally\xc2\xa0on board. \xc2\xa0Particularly for this:Maybe\xc2\xa0only an opera\xc2\xa0could do justice to the scope of the forces at work [in the clash between Robert Moses and Jane Jacobs on urban planning], and pretty soon we\xe2\x80\x99ll have one.[...][T]he team has been working hard to distill the narrative essence of the Moses-Jacobs conflict, which the opera frames as a love triangle\xe2\x80\x94with both Jacobs and Moses \xe2\x80\x9cvying for the love of the city.\xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x80\x9cThe biggest challenge is we don\xe2\x80\x99t want to make this, Moses is Darth Vader and Jacobs is a perfect angel from heaven,\xe2\x80\x9d says Frankel. \xe2\x80\x9cIt\xe2\x80\x99s more interesting artistically to see them both as human beings with strengths and weaknesses. We are figuring out how to do it with Moses more easily. Jacobs is more difficult. She is just so darn right, so much.\xe2\x80\x9d\xc2\xa0For more Quick Takes, visit Conversion Diary!'
